Topic: Advanced Microsoft Word Techniques

Solved Practical - Format and align text, Formatting Paragraphs, Line and paragraph spacing, using FIND and REPLACE, setting line spacing, add bullet and numbers in lists, add borders and shading, document views, Page settings and margins, Spelling and Grammatical checks
Solution

1. Format and Align Text
Formatting Text:
•	Bold: Select the text and press Ctrl + B.
•	Italic: Select the text and press Ctrl + I.
•	Underline: Select the text and press Ctrl + U.
Aligning Text:
•	Left Align: Select the text and press Ctrl + L.
•	Center Align: Select the text and press Ctrl + E.
•	Right Align: Select the text and press Ctrl + R.
•	Justify: Select the text and press Ctrl + J.
2. Formatting Paragraphs
•	Indenting Paragraphs: Increase Indent: Click the Increase Indent button on the toolbar or press Ctrl + M.
•	Decrease Indent: Click the Decrease Indent button on the toolbar or press Ctrl + Shift + M.
 3. Paragraph Alignment:
•	Align paragraphs using the same shortcuts as for text alignment (Ctrl + L, Ctrl + E, Ctrl + R, Ctrl + J).
4. Line and Paragraph Spacing
•	Line Spacing: Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click on Line Spacing. Choose the desired spacing (e.g., 1.0, 1.5, 2.0).
•	Paragraph Spacing: Adjust spacing before and after paragraphs using the Line Spacing Options.


5. Using FIND and REPLACE
•	Find: Press Ctrl + F, enter the word or phrase you want to find.
•	Replace: Press Ctrl + H, enter the word or phrase to find and the word or phrase to replace it with, then click Replace or Replace All.
6. Setting Line Spacing
•	Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click Line and Paragraph Spacing, then select the desired line spacing option.
7. Adding Bullets and Numbers in Lists
•	Bulleted List: Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click Bullets.
•	Numbered List: Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click Numbering.
8. Adding Borders and Shading
•	Borders: Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click Borders, then select the desired border option.
•	Shading: Go to the Home tab, in the Paragraph group, click Shading, then select the desired shading color.
9. Document Views
•	Read Mode: Go to the View tab, click Read Mode.
•	Print Layout: Go to the View tab, click Print Layout.
•	Web Layout: Go to the View tab, click Web Layout.
10. Page Settings and Margins
•	Page Orientation: Go to the Layout tab, in the Page Setup group, click Orientation, then select Portrait or Landscape.
•	Margins: Go to the Layout tab, in the Page Setup group, click Margins, and then select the desired margin setting.
11. Spelling and Grammatical Checks
•	Spelling Check: Press F7, or go to the Review tab, in the Proofing group, click Spelling & Grammar.
•	Grammar Check: Errors will be underlined in blue. Right-click the underlined text for suggestions.
